segment.source: The Internet Explorer - Web Site Report screen shows the following information for each of the websites visited in your organization:
segment.target: The Internet Explorer - Web Site Report screen shows the following information for each of the websites visited in your organization:

segment.source: The website URL.
segment.target: The website URL.

segment.source: Your organization's compatibility rating for the website.
segment.target: Your organization's compatibility rating for the website.

segment.source: The count of issues for the website.
segment.target: The count of issues for the website.

segment.source: The count of resolved issues for the website.
segment.target: The count of resolved issues for the website.

segment.source: To open the Internet Explorer - Web Site Report screen
segment.target: To open the Internet Explorer - Web Site Report screen

segment.source: In Application Compatibility Manager (ACM), on the Quick Reports pane, click Analyze.
segment.target: In Application Compatibility Manager (ACM), on the Quick Reports pane, click Analyze.

segment.source: In the Quick Reports pane, under the Internet Explorer heading, click Web Sites.
segment.target: In the Quick Reports pane, under the Internet Explorer heading, click Web Sites.

segment.target: Using the Internet Explorer - Web Site Report Screen
